~ $ git add --all
~ $ git commit -m "Initial commit"
~ $ git push -u origin master
always remember to use this to update onto github "everyday".

after I have the repository I start to install the jekyll.
sudo apt-get install gem
sudo gem install jekyll
**Notice:
	I faced a problem while I am installing the jekyll:
**********************************************************
Building native extensions.  This could take a while...
ERROR:  Error installing jekyll:
	ERROR: Failed to build gem native extension.
current directory: /var/lib/gems/2.3.0/gems/ffi-1.9.18/ext/ffi_c
/usr/bin/ruby2.3 -r ./siteconf20170315-13277-ucav6r.rb extconf.rb
mkmf.rb can't find header files for ruby at /usr/lib/ruby/include/ruby.h
**********************************************************
So the solution is to install ruby-dev, I am using Ubuntu 16.04 and this is also works for Debian user.
	sudo apt-get install ruby-dev

For some Fedora user, this solution might work:
	yum -y install gcc mysql-devel ruby-devel rubygems
	gem install -y mysql -- --with-mysql-config=/usr/bin/mysql_config

